# ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 54/120 – Cumulative Maximum

## 🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to calculate the **highest salary seen so far** within each department.

---

## 📊 Input Dataset

| department | employee | salary |
| ---------- | -------- | -----: |
| IT         | John     |  60000 |
| IT         | Alice    |  70000 |
| IT         | Bob      |  65000 |
| HR         | David    |  45000 |
| HR         | Sam      |  50000 |

---

## ✅ Expected Output

| department | employee | salary | max_salary_so_far |
| ---------- | -------- | -----: | ----------------: |
| IT         | John     |  60000 |             60000 |
| IT         | Bob      |  65000 |             65000 |
| IT         | Alice    |  70000 |             70000 |
| HR         | David    |  45000 |             45000 |
| HR         | Sam      |  50000 |             50000 |

---

## ✅ Recommended Solution

```python
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark.sql.functions import max, col

window_spec = (
    Window.partitionBy("department")
          .orderBy(col("salary"))
          .rowsBetween(Window.unboundedPreceding, Window.currentRow)
)

df.withColumn(
    "max_salary_so_far",
